vDfoUXxN8YJKRu2ZcGqqoEUZ0M1i5cLEoMTBhGbdMdpeuOZyHaEHDD-QzRSBB3xH3cuNfN_ZdbTObDxl2CAFyW465oLGP1qatFvfqz7RBLI09bfBxbZ4Aj3A2vpQDGvDrHYmvZzBaTVHZdZS3tJ2VMGzgoMD2lgvJB2f72dJlNgYck7e-21b2IUeytibA2dbz8bc2_Cui38u7XkFMNW9H9HhOEM0cwF2M8EL9pjatECHXF7jJoKaC8nEYBR2EkheTF0Q20n5UlNQFXKpTUX9w-AMLR5mF\">&nbsp;a few issues ago</a>&nbsp;when I recommended the book,&nbsp;<em><a href=\"https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJwlkc2upCAQhZ-m2WkEVHDB4m7uaxh-CpsMgoFyjPP0g91JhZ8cTurUh9UIWy63OnJF8iwr3geoBFeNgAiFnBXKGpxig2ALE5w4NToqJ0lCXX0B2HWICssJ5DhNDFZjyOlx8IlJRt5KeL9INxojqRfSiWFwYKwxgmovKeXfvvp0AZIFBX-h3DkBieqNeLz4z4v9trquq79CjEHvPuMbSkjbW--9zXtTj5LdabGdmtRtBdpkFbvngmGH2unkuhg8dNl3pnWInTkL5tQcJLTpGG21UDkMlPe0N8us2cRhATtaPks-OTsaS73RGhyTr3HYN9bX01TU9s-TghRldYS7b1TwX3tgbxtbSAxH_eiNz9r2_UwB7xWSNhHcFx1-f-ADc90gQWn53apR0ZlyMYmZTvMiv6getkzQUSyUtAAuN1dSu95DLHBAjFD-A-ZNooc\">The Greatest: The Times and Life of Beryl Burton</a></em>&nbsp;by William Fotheringham and mentioned how ‚Äî not only did I learn about one of the best cyclists of all time ‚Äî I discovered many women cyclists‚Äô names from the past I had never heard before.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This week, then, if you‚Äôre not already familiar with&nbsp;<strong>Yvonne Reynders</strong>&nbsp;then here are some facts and further reading about this Belgian legend of women‚Äôs cycling:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Reynders competed during the 1960s in both road and track.</li><li>She began her sporting life in athletics before switching to discus.</li><li>She started out her cycling life by delivering coal bags weighing 10kg each after she left school aged 16.</li><li>She won 13 medals at world championships; three golds on the track and four on the road.&nbsp;</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n\n\n\n<h2>That‚Äôs All üëã</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Thanks for reading Women‚Äôs Cycling Weekly! If you‚Äôre new here and you like what WCW is doing and would like to support it then you can do so via Ko-Fi:</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://email.mg2.substack.com